***************************************************Activity 1: Install terraform on Ubuntu ec2****************************************
Terraform doc to see AWS resources information
https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/2.43.0/docs

Step 1: Create one Ubuntu EC2 instance and connect to it using instance connect

Step 2 : Install Terraform on Ubuntu ec2 instance

Link https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/install?product_intent=terraform#linux

Type following commands
wget -O - https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg

echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg] https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(lsb_release -cs) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/hashicorp.list

sudo apt update && sudo apt install terraform

Step 3: Check if installation is successful by typing following command
terraform version

Step 4: Install AWS CLI on Ubuntu ec2 instance : To connect to AWS i need AWS cLI.

sudo apt update
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
sudo apt install unzip
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install

Step 5: Check if AWS CLI installation is successful 
aws --version

Step 6: Login into AWS
aws configure
Enter access key and secrete access key and set default version as us-east-1
--------------
Step 7: check if login is successful
aws sts get-caller-identity

*****************************************************Activity 2: Install terraform on laptop*********************************

Link https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/install?product_intent=terraform#windows

1.	Click on windows binary version 386 download and It will download zip
2.	Unzip the file and copy the path
3.	Go to control panel
4.	Open system
5.	Open Advance system settings
6.	Click on environment variable button
7.	Select path  edit - new - paste the path copied earlier
8.	Create folder demo anywhere in laptop
9.	Right click and open github bash
10.	Check if installation is successful using following command
	terraform version 
11.	Download and Install aws cli
	https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/getting-started-install.html

12.	Check aws installation 
	aws –-version

13.	Login in AWS using 
	aws configure
	Enter access key and secrete access key

14.	Step 6: check if login is successful
	aws sts get-caller-identity
